PRETORIA - The African National Congress (ANC) will be hosting an election manifesto consultative workshop on Monday. President Cyril Ramaphosa delivered the keynote address at the workshop. He said that just like the Freedom Charter, the ANC people's manifesto will be a revolutionary document. According to Ramaphosa, South Africans need to work hand-in-hand with government to create the society they want. WATCH: Former President Jacob #Zuma on his way to join one of the 9 working groups at the #ANCworkshop that will draft the party’s election manifesto. @eNCA pic.twitter.com/dKmmnRVBjL — African National Congress (@MYANC) June 22, 2018 ANC hosts the national Manifesto Workshop today in Tshwane, Gauteng. Arrivals & registration are currently underway. #PeoplesManifesto pic.twitter.com/SWL9BiBKTU eNCA